Scores of indigenes of Eruwa in Oyo State on Friday organised a candlelight procession for late Timothy Adegoke. Adegoke, a chartered accountant, was an indigene of Eruwa in Ibarapa East Local Government Area of the state. He left behind three children, a wife and an aged mother. DAILY POST recalls that Adegoke was until his death, a Masters in Business Administration (MBA) student at the Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU), Ile-Ife, Osun State. The deceased was allegedly killed last year in a hotel he lodged. Adegoke lodged in the hotel in order to write one of his examinations in the university the following day. The owner of the hotel, Mr Rahman Adedoyin, and some staff of the hotel have been arrested in connection with his murder, DAILY POST gathered. Our correspondent gathered that the deceasedâ€™s body was released to his family on Friday and taken to Eruwa, where he will be buried on Saturday. The indigenes among whom are youths, women and men described the killing of Adegoke as unfortunate, calling for the prosecution of his killers.